sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
This action creates a new user on the Box account of the associated credentials.

Inputs:

  • Name - Full Name of user. E.g. John Smith.
  • Email ID - The Email ID of the user. This will be set as the login username.
  • Job Title - The user's job title. E.g. Trainee
  • Phone - The user's phone number.
  • Address - The user's address.
  • Space Amount - The user’s total available space amount in gigabyte.
  • Status - Status of newly created user. Can be set to Active, Inactive, Cannot Delete Edit, or Cannot Delete Edit Upload.
  • Can See Managed Users - Flag to set whether the user can see managed users.
  • Is External Collab Restricted - Flag to set whether the user is restricted from external collaboration.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".
  • User ID - ID of the created user. Will be populated in case of success.
  • User Info - Information of the created user in JSON format. Will be populated in case of success.
  • User Details - Information of the created user.
    • ID
    • Type
    • Job Title
    • Language
    • Avatar URL

Error Messages:

  • Invalid username or password/token.
  • User with the specified login already exists.
  • Invalid input parameters in request.
  • The credentials associated with the Box Spoke connection does not have enough permission to perform this action.

To use this action, the corresponding Box connection and credential must be created and associated with the Box Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
